Install Notes
=============

Zulip is a group communication tool.

https://zulip.com/hello

Configuration Fields
--------------------

1. **Email** - The user to authenticate as.
2. **Api Key** - The API key associated with the provided user. See: https://zulip.com/#settings
3. **Stream** - The Zulip stream where you want messages to be sent.  (If you leave this blank, it defaults to the "commits" stream in Zulip.)  Whether you use the default stream or specify it explicitly, you need to set up the stream on the Zulip side.
4. **Commit Stream** - The Zulip stream where you want git traffic to go to. Defaults to **Stream** if unset.
5. **Issue Stream** - The Zulip stream where you want Github issues traffic to go to. Defaults to **Stream** if unset.
6. **Branches** - If you want to restrict Zulip notifications to certain GitHub branches, then provide a comma delimited list of git branches here (e.g. `master,staging,prod`).  Otherwise, leave it empty.

Checkboxes
----------

1. **block_pull_requests** - Block Github pull requests traffic.
2. **block_issues** - Block Github issues traffic.
3. **block_commits** - Block git traffic.
